==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Proportionable
<hw>Pro*por"tion*a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Capable of
being proportioned, or made proportional; also, proportional;
proportionate.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Pro*por"tion*a*ble*ness</wf>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>But eloquence may exist without a <qex>proportionable</qex> degree
of wisdom.</q> <rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q> <qex>Proportionable</qex>, which is no longer much favored, was
of our [i. e., English writers'] own coining.</q> <rj><qau>Fitzed.
Hall.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Proportionably</ent>⟦br⟧
